Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.92,0:01:42.95,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.54,0:01:45.74,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Morning, Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.76,0:01:48.00,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Stella.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.00,0:01:50.46,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? You look shocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.77,0:01:54.42,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Er, I didn't think you'd actually come by.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.15,0:01:57.26,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not a liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.31,0:02:02.89,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I-It must be cold. Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.89,0:02:03.93,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.97,0:02:11.23,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, this is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.23,0:02:12.85,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,You made all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.85,0:02:14.88,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's not a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.88,0:02:16.34,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,It was our contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.34,0:02:19.61,Default,Edgedad,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you should be \Nwandering out by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.10,0:02:23.36,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,No one's going to abduct \Nme right after Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.36,0:02:26.74,Default,Edgedad,0000,0000,0000,,You were abducted {\i1}on{\i0} Christmas, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.74,0:02:28.35,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.35,0:02:29.59,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.97,0:02:34.52,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,I thought a mage's home would \Nhave a more ominous vibe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.52,0:02:36.03,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,But it's spacious and clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.03,0:02:37.50,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.39,0:02:41.77,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I shouldn't tell her there's\N all kinds of creatures on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.38,0:02:50.32,Default,Edgedad,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be in my study.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.32,0:02:52.21,Default,Edgedad,0000,0000,0000,,You can enjoy yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.76,0:02:56.82,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.87,0:03:00.47,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.97,0:03:02.78,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Want to come to my room?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.78,0:03:03.75,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.94,0:03:07.70,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,I smell herbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.68,0:03:10.16,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,When are you going back to London?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.38,0:03:11.28,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.70,0:03:13.46,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,I'll come hang out again next month,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.46,0:03:14.68,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,so you come to my place, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.55,0:03:16.30,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.07,0:03:19.46,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,This is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.46,0:03:21.21,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to take some with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.21,0:03:23.06,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.06,0:03:24.44,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,In return for the snacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.82,0:03:28.13,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,A return for a return... It's gonna\Nbe Christmas every time we meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.02,0:03:32.06,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Stella,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.02,0:03:36.07,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,it's been a long time \Nsince I've made a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.53,0:03:38.19,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.94,0:03:43.40,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,It'd help if you could tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.14,0:03:48.84,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Invite me to do whatever you want to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.84,0:03:50.44,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,and just talk with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.44,0:03:52.86,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,What if they don't like it, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.16,0:03:58.23,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,You're obviously not the \Nsame person as your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.23,0:04:00.68,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,You're obviously not gonna \Nhave all the same interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.38,0:04:04.15,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Words aren't for understanding each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.15,0:04:06.37,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,They exist for the sake \Nof talking to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.78,0:04:12.15,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Or so my Dad says, but honestly, \Na jerk is a jerk from beginning to end.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.38,0:04:15.99,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,You're so mature, Stella.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.60,0:04:18.80,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you're about my age.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.80,0:04:20.26,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,I hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.06,0:04:23.27,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, how old are you again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.27,0:04:24.28,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,I'm ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.74,0:04:25.39,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.39,0:04:26.30,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.08,0:04:28.34,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Ten...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.34,0:04:29.41,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,How about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.57,0:04:32.34,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Almost sixteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.03,0:04:45.27,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I'd decided I would say what I mean \Nto say, but it's pretty hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.27,0:04:46.77,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Let's practice, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.55,0:04:48.77,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Practice?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.77,0:04:50.67,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be selfish, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.67,0:04:52.80,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Although you don't seem like you would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.96,0:04:56.32,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really selfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.76,0:05:00.48,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hoping to come over to your place soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.48,0:05:03.08,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,That's not practice, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.08,0:05:04.76,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,That's just a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.82,0:05:19.93,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Elias...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.23,0:05:24.45,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Silky, did he leave a note?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.54,0:05:29.59,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.43,0:05:33.98,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Ruth, can you walk Stella home?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.98,0:05:36.50,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, are you going after him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.50,0:05:38.14,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.35,0:05:43.79,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,You're both strangely dishonest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.58,0:05:47.14,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Stella. Let's hang \Nout again sometime.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.65,0:05:51.38,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,What's up with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.38,0:05:53.35,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,"Say what she means to say"...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.70,0:05:58.74,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,She talks more with her arms \Nand legs than with her mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.52,0:06:09.26,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use. He keeps getting further.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.62,0:06:10.89,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,What's gotten into him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.75,0:06:38.36,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take on the form I need to \Ntake to do what needs to be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.65,0:06:41.61,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I can't keep up with the legs of a fox.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.25,0:06:44.44,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I'd be too big with the body of a bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.58,0:06:47.90,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I have to run faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.90,0:06:49.58,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I have to run further.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.05,0:06:53.45,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I have to catch him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.13,0:06:56.71,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,This is my wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.40,0:07:03.35,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, did you hear something?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.35,0:07:04.62,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It sounded like a wolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.62,0:07:05.90,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Probably a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.90,0:07:08.41,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's looking for \Nits pack or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.53,0:07:36.87,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.77,0:07:41.09,Default,Edgedad,0000,0000,0000,,You're a proper wolf this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.81,0:07:52.69,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.38,0:07:57.40,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry if we were making too much noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.24,0:08:00.03,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be more careful next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.06,0:08:05.34,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Do you feel all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.68,0:08:09.86,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something that upset you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.53,0:08:13.69,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Elias?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.93,0:08:21.82,Default,Edgedad,0000,0000,0000,,Listening to your voices oddly \Nmade me want to leave home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.84,0:08:25.63,Default,Edgedad,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted Stella to go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.40,0:08:29.82,Default,Edgedad,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I wanted to be alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.38,0:08:33.64,Default,Edgedad,0000,0000,0000,,but as soon as I knew you were \Nchasing me, I felt better.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.85,0:08:39.18,Default,Edgedad,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, I couldn't stop running.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.98,0:08:41.27,Default,Edgedad,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.27,0:08:42.04,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.58,0:08:53.47,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we go home and have tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.76,0:09:07.82,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Elias must be more confused \Nabout himself than he realizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.23,0:09:14.41,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I thought he was leaving me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.30,0:09:23.08,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Elias might have been the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.12,0:09:31.83,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Can I allow myself the conceit of thinking \Nthat's how much he thinks of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.17,0:09:35.79,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,You're in a good mood, Stella.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.32,0:09:38.73,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,When are we going to \NGrandma's place next time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.73,0:09:40.53,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,You're so impatient.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.06,0:09:42.80,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.43,0:09:46.85,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.06,0:09:57.06,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.21,0:10:00.95,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Are they not home yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.26,0:10:05.61,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take another look around.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.48,0:10:21.44,Magus-Internal/narrator,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Our connection's being interrupted.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.51,0:10:23.95,Magus-Internal/narrator,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Chise, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.66,0:10:31.33,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,This might be bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.33,0:10:32.69,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.78,0:10:33.70,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Elias!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.23,0:10:39.33,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Ruth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.40,0:10:40.32,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Ruth!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.56,0:10:43.35,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,He's going to eat me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.18,0:10:45.52,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,He's going to consume me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.15,0:10:47.22,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.27,0:10:50.01,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,That's not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.48,0:10:52.94,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want that right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.97,0:11:06.65,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.78,0:11:10.73,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.19,0:11:24.16,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Which shadow?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.11,0:11:29.05,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.90,0:11:42.81,Default,Little Green Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Are you looking for your master?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.77,0:11:45.96,Magus-Internal/narrator,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Is she...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.98,0:11:55.94,Default,Little Green Woman,0000,0000,0000,,You all made an offering of raindrop\N fruits and branches to Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.57,0:12:01.02,Default,Little Green Woman,0000,0000,0000,,In return, I'll lend you my flame.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.59,0:12:11.70,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.49,0:12:18.91,Default,Little Green Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Next winter, when I become Mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.91,0:12:22.00,Default,Little Green Woman,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you'll offer me raindrop \Nfruits and branches again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.95,0:12:25.69,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.16,0:12:26.93,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.21,0:12:28.15,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.37,0:12:30.14,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Ruth...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.46,0:12:31.27,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.27,0:12:32.21,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.21,0:12:33.36,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.36,0:12:34.47,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.47,0:12:35.74,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Is it Elias?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.48,0:12:37.19,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.66,0:12:41.08,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I think he had some kind \Nof temper tantrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.08,0:12:42.07,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,A tantrum?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.49,0:12:48.00,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,What did my mom tell me in these situations?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.54,0:13:00.79,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,What you're feeling is probably \Nwhat's called jealousy, Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.00,0:13:06.28,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,A feeling of envy, of wondering \Nwhy you're singled out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.37,0:13:11.54,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,But being jealous of someone—\Nof something...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.54,0:13:16.05,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Being envious or resentful \Nwill only bring you misery.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.29,0:13:20.07,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,That's not something you're \Nmeant to throw at people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.65,0:13:24.32,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,It's something you have to \Ndeal with inside yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.31,0:13:32.06,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I'm the most envious of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.20,0:13:34.60,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Do you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.59,0:13:41.51,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Keep being selfish, and I'll have \Nto take matters into my own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.51,0:13:42.63,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Ruth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.74,0:13:46.38,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.38,0:13:48.22,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,There's no telling where \Nthis knife will land!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.19,0:14:10.86,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Are you done now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.61,0:14:13.71,Default,Octodad,0000,0000,0000,,You really scared me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.16,0:14:14.74,Default,Octodad,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.32,0:14:18.34,Default,Octodad,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.63,0:14:21.95,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.57,0:14:24.50,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not angry anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.80,0:14:27.33,Default,Octodad,0000,0000,0000,,So you were angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.80,0:14:28.83,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,A bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.36,0:14:32.67,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Let's talk lots when we get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.02,0:14:34.22,Default,Octodad,0000,0000,0000,,Talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.83,0:14:35.69,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.69,0:14:36.76,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Together.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.23,0:14:41.53,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Stella taught me a lot today, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.92,0:14:44.73,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like for you to listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.73,0:14:48.86,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Let's stay up for a while in bed to talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.43,0:14:55.85,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,and fall asleep together tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.80,0:15:00.24,Default,Chessboard,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, let's go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.64,0:15:04.46,Default,Octodad,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.15,0:15:12.53,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,They were like father and daughter \Nuntil just the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.57,0:15:16.88,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Now they're like mother and son.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.61,0:15:33.81,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,I'm leaving now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.33,0:15:42.27,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.23,0:15:49.46,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hello, is Angelica-san available?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.22,0:15:53.79,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.79,0:15:57.25,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm David Burley. Angie's husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.84,0:16:08.46,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, do you think you \Ncould wait for a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.46,0:16:09.83,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.11,0:16:14.13,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,Are you a mage, too, David-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.57,0:16:16.55,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm an ordinary human.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.55,0:16:18.51,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm lucky enough to both have a job,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.51,0:16:20.88,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,and have a good relationship\N with my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.88,0:16:22.96,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Other than that, I'm nothing special.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.96,0:16:25.10,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, is there a visitor—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.63,0:16:27.43,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.37,0:16:30.73,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.78,0:16:39.12,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, she's been a bit difficult lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.12,0:16:40.11,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.11,0:16:42.79,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,I just met a similar kid recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.31,0:16:45.87,Default,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,David, did you call me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.27,0:16:52.90,Default,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Ainsworth's not waking up?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.90,0:16:56.32,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,Not since the night of the 26th.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.50,0:17:01.90,Magus-Flashback,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sleepy?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.82,0:17:20.49,Magus-Flashback,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, where do you bloom?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.52,0:17:28.00,Magus-Flashback,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,Under the window where the children sleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.64,0:17:36.01,Magus-Flashback,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,white flowers on the night of a pale moon...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.75,0:17:44.38,Magus-Flashback,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,Three, four, where do you bloom?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.89,0:17:51.64,Magus-Flashback,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,On the frame of Mother's mirror,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.64,0:17:58.60,Magus-Flashback,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,a little blue flower blooms...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.89,0:18:01.26,Default,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,You sang him a lullaby, and he fell asleep?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.26,0:18:02.33,Default,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That{\i0} thing did?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.33,0:18:03.37,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,That thing did.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.96,0:18:08.73,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,I did some research, too, but I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.34,0:18:12.50,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,You say that, but you tried a few things.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.50,0:18:14.33,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.76,0:18:21.41,Default,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,If your magic compounded with \Nyour song, that's magic itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.41,0:18:22.50,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,Magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.81,0:18:26.36,Default,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't normally happen \Nunless you intend it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.86,0:18:31.13,Default,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,but that might be your talent, Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.83,0:18:32.96,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,My talent?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.66,0:18:37.37,Magus-Internal/narrator,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,Then why am I bad at making sleeping aids?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.03,0:18:40.31,Default,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,Just a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.75,0:18:42.44,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.29,0:18:44.40,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,Angelica-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.80,0:18:48.18,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the bracelet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.63,0:18:51.23,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to get you \Nsomething next Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.90,0:18:54.59,Default,Angry,0000,0000,0000,,I look forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.28,0:18:59.62,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Want some more tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.09,0:19:02.14,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,I'm good, thank—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.89,0:19:03.90,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.74,0:19:07.41,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You should get some sleep there \Nif you're not feeling well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.18,0:19:11.11,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you often push yourself too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.55,0:19:13.57,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.02,0:19:20.35,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You can't really go to \Nthe hospital for it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.09,0:19:23.07,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You should take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.07,0:19:24.71,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,You know about that, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.62,0:19:30.47,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,There's someone who talks about \Nyou like you're her own child.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.30,0:19:37.32,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Angie hasn't changed ever since I met her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.27,0:19:41.04,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'd been asking her out ever \Nsince I was a snotty brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.04,0:19:44.92,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,After more years than I \Ncan count on two hands,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.35,0:19:47.32,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,she finally accepted.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.78,0:19:52.20,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It was only after our daughter was born
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.20,0:19:56.21,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,that I finally got a sense of why \Nshe'd always turned me down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.10,0:19:59.73,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.87,0:20:03.27,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have to think about dying by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.73,0:20:05.23,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,But Angie...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.05,0:20:07.61,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Our daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.05,0:20:12.68,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,They have to continue sending people \Noff, and there's no end in sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.82,0:20:18.94,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's painful to think about how many days \Nare left that we can laugh together.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.29,0:20:24.72,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,But unlike me, if things pan \Nout for you, you can keep up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.89,0:20:30.21,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,So let's live as long as we can \Nwithout stressing or forcing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.21,0:20:33.04,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You and I both.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.64,0:20:39.95,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.23,0:20:47.50,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.50,0:20:59.29,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Yo, Chise, want some he—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.65,0:21:06.65,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, you're awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.11,0:21:10.44,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,Was it the medicine or was it {\i1}that{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.84,0:21:13.21,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness, Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.68,0:21:15.20,Default,Scary mom,0000,0000,0000,,I was so worried...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.01,0:21:26.17,Default,Dorf,0000,0000,0000,,I'll explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.31,0:21:38.41,Default,Dudley,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to get in trouble\Nfor coming out this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.41,0:21:39.75,Default,Barney,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.75,0:21:42.30,Default,Dudley,0000,0000,0000,,But kids aren't supposed to \Ngo this far. It's not safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.30,0:21:44.12,Default,Barney,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, there's something shiny!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.12,0:21:45.66,Default,Dudley,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.55,0:21:55.65,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.56,0:22:00.55,Default,Dragon dad,0000,0000,0000,,Poachers, yet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.63,0:22:03.19,Default,Dragon dad,0000,0000,0000,,Fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.70,0:22:06.02,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's the caretaker!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.49,0:22:09.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surrender and return to the soil.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.86,0:22:14.43,Default,Guygirl,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you, mister caretaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.46,0:23:58.32,Default,Guygirl,0000,0000,0000,,The wandering sorcerer, \NJoseph, is on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.16,0:24:04.37,Default,Guygirl,0000,0000,0000,,Joseph's scheming leads the girl \Nand the mage to frantic London.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.77,0:24:09.47,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Depending on price and terms,\N I'll take on your work.
